{"lemma":"ناجِذَيْ","slug":"ناجِذَيْ","root":"ن.ج.ذ","root_slug":"ن-ج-ذ","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-ج-ذ","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n39408"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%AC%D9%90%D8%B0%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"premolar tooth"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of نَجَذَ (najaḏa, “to bite vehemently”)."},"ipa":["/naː.d͡ʒið/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n39408","headword_ar":"ناجِذ","root":"nj*","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"sing. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nawaAji*u","text_ar":"نَوَاجِذُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"furthest of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aDoraAs","text_ar":"اَضْرَاس"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"molar teeth"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (S, A, L, Msb, K,) of a man; (S, Msb;) which are four in number, (S, L, Msb, K,) next after the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"OaroHa'=","text_ar":"Oَرْحَء="},{"kind":"text","text":"; (L;) also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aDoraAsu AlHulumi","text_ar":"اَضْرَاسُ الحُلُمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"teeth of puberty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aDoraAsu AlEaqoli","text_ar":"اَضْرَاسُ العَقْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wisdom-teeth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S, Mgh, L, Msb,) because they grow after the attaining to puberty, and the completion of the intellectual faculties: (S, L, Msb:) or all the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ADrAs","text_ar":"اضراس"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"molar-teeth"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"teeth next behind the canine teeth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, Msb, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"altogether four in number:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, Msb:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"canine teeth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, Msb, K:) which last, accord. to Th, (L, Msb,) or the last but one, accord. to IAth, (L,) is the signification meant in the trad. (respecting Mohammad, L.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaHika","text_ar":"ضَحِكَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hat~aY badato nawaAji*uhu","text_ar":"حَتَّى بَدَتْ نَوَاجِذُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He laughed so that his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nwAj*","text_ar":"نواجذ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"appeared"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (L, Msb;) because Mohammad's utmost laugh was slight; or this is a hyperbolical expression, not meant to be literally understood; for the signification of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nwAj*","text_ar":"نواجذ"},{"kind":"text","text":"most commonly obtaining is the first of those given above: (L:) the phrase also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he laughed violently,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"immoderately:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L:) the term"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nwAj*","text_ar":"نواجذ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also sometimes used in relation to the horse, (S, L,) or a solid-hoofed animal, as well as man; (Bári', Msb;) and they are [termed] the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anoyaAb","text_ar":"اَنْيَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"in a soft-footed animal such as the camel; and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawaAlig","text_ar":"سَوَالِغ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in a cloven-hoofed animal. (S, L.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sin~N","text_ar":"سِنٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaD~uwA EalayohaA biAln~awaAji*i","text_ar":"عَضُّوا عَلَيْهَا بِالنَّوَاجِذِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They held her fast. as one holds fast in biting with all his grinders."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, from a trad.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abodaY","text_ar":"اَبْدَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAji*ahu","text_ar":"نَاجِذَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was immoderate in his laughter:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in his anger."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaD~ EalaY naAji*ihi","text_ar":"عَضّ عَلَى نَاجِذِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He attained to the age of puberty;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of manly vigour;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of firmness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soundness, of judgment:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, L, K: *) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he bacame patient, and firm, vigorous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hardy, in the management of affairs."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balaga fiY AlEilomi wagayorihi binaAji*ihi","text_ar":"بَلَغَ فِى العِلْمِ وَغَيْرِهِ بِنَاجِذِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made his knowledge, &c., sound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"firm."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badato","text_ar":"بَدَتْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nawaAji*uhu","text_ar":"نَوَاجِذُهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nwAj*","text_ar":"نواجذ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"appeared"},{"kind":"text","text":"by reason of anger or of laughter. (L.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","L","Msb","K","Mgh"]}]}}